                            <comment id="12978853" author="joe.luo" created="Tue, 24 Jun 2014 06:39:28 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks to me that concurrent accessing to the file instance.properties might not be an issue. But rather, properties that were stored in a list somehow got concurrently modified even before the data could be written to the property file (instance.properties). Thus it caused either empty file or out of sync status from the child containers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
